Issues found: 2
  - [FIXED] Lint error: unused variable in agent-ticket-assignment test
    Root cause: test/agent-ticket-assignment.test.ts:177 declared `let resolveAgentFromLabels` but never assigned/used.
    Left over from when the test was written to test the private function directly, before deciding to test indirectly via fullSync.
    Fix: removed unused variable declaration. Commit: TBD

  - [FIXED] enrichPrDescription JSON parsing fails when Claude wraps output in markdown code fences
    Root cause: enrichPrDescription calls `claude -p --output-format text`, which should return plain text.
    But Claude (haiku) sometimes wraps JSON in ```json...``` code fences despite the prompt saying not to.
    The existing `{`-walker used `JSON.parse(rawOutput.slice(pos))` which fails on trailing ` ``` ` because
    JSON.parse rejects trailing non-whitespace content. Result: "no valid JSON with title+body found" warning
    for every PR — the PR description enrichment never applied.
    Fix: (1) strip markdown code fences from rawOutput before parsing; (2) when walking `{` positions, also try
    parsing `slice(pos, lastBrace+1)` instead of only `slice(pos)`. Added 2 regression tests.
    Commit: TBD

